  "event": {
    "top_event": "Employee struck by falling coring barrel",
    "incident_type": "Other Injury",
    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "All operations on the drill floor were stopped following the incident",
      "Injured Party was sent to the onboard Medic for evaluation",
      "Injured Party was sent onshore for physician evaluation",
      "Injured Party was placed on Restricted Work duty"
    ],
    "summary": "On October 22, 2015, while performing drilling operations on Statoil's #002 well, an employee working on the drill floor of the Discoverer Americas was struck on the foot by a coring barrel while retrieving a sample from the wellbore. The coring barrel became hung up on a hang off pin on the transport rack, forming slack in the suspension line. As the Driller picked up on the block to readjust the barrel, it shifted and fell to the deck, striking a Floorhand on his left foot. The employee sustained a fractured toe and was placed on Restricted Work duty.",
